On November 5, 2015, the President signed several bills into law. H.R. 313, the "Wounded Warriors Federal Leave Act of 2015," provides leave to newly-hired Federal employees who are veterans with a service-connected disability of 30 percent or more. H.R. 322 designates a United States Postal Service facility in Missouri as the Sgt. Zachary M. Fisher Post Office. H.R. 323 designates another USPS facility in Missouri as the Sgt. Amanda N. Pinson Post Office. H.R. 324 designates a USPS facility in Missouri as the Lt. Daniel P. Riordan Post Office. H.R. 558 designates a USPS facility in Ohio as the Richard "Dick" Chenault Post Office Building. H.R. 623, the "DHS Social Media Improvement Act of 2015," requires the Department of Homeland Security to establish a Social Media Working Group. H.R. 774, the "Illegal, Unreported, and Unregulated Fishing Enforcement Act of 2015," enhances enforcement authorities against illegal fishing. H.R. 1442 designates a USPS facility in New York as the Staff Sergeant Robert H. Dietz Post Office Building. H.R. 1884 designates another USPS facility in New York as the Officer Daryl R. Pierson Memorial Post Office Building. H.R. 3059 designates a USPS facility in Oklahoma as the James Robert Kalsu Post Office Building. S. 1362 allows for the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services to waive certain requirements for testing innovative payment and delivery models. S. 2162, the "Librarian of Congress Succession Modernization Act of 2015," establishes a 10-year term for the Librarian of Congress.